item.description:
Jean-Louis Loday&rsquo;s realisation of the (5-)associahedron:
The vertices are generated from planar binary trees using the algorithm described in Loday&rsquo;s paper1 (Loday gives vertices in 4-space but they sit in a 3-dimsional hyperplane which I&rsquo;ve projected onto ordinary 3-space). The surface was created and written to STL with the Trimesh Python library. Code.
Loday, J-L. Realization of the Stasheff polytope. Archiv der Mathematik 83, 267–278 (2004). doi&#160;&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;
